radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is fluid-filled, hyperemic, with surrounding inflammatory changes measuring up to 10 mm. No pneumoperitoneum or abscess present. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are normal. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No abdominal aortic aneurysm or atherosclerotic disease.
